\begin{align*}
\mean*[\Gr']t(v)
& = \mean[\Gr_2']s\\
& = \Apply{\mean*[\Gr_2]{\Derive s}}{\mean*[\Gr_2]s}\\
& = \Apply{\D f(v)(\Diff vv)}{f(v)}\\
& = \Apply*{\mean*[\Gr]{\Derive t}}{\mean*[\Gr]t}(v).
\end{align*}
Since $v$ is arbitrary, $\mean*[\Gr']t$ and
